## kaslr-seed

**Value type:** `<u64>`

A 64-bit value provided by firmware or bootloader to seed the kernel address space layout randomization (KASLR). The value should be a cryptographically random number. When present in the `/chosen` node, the Linux kernel uses it as entropy for KASLR.

```dts
chosen {
    kaslr-seed = <0xdeadbeef 0xcafebabe>;
};
```
